#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn2.29"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.29:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.29:0.2"
msgid "3. Nānātitthiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Various Sectarians "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.29:0.3"
msgid "29. Susimasutta "
msgstr "29. With Susīma "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.147, sc1
msgctxt "sn2.29:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.29:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him, "

# NOTE: BB’s “approve of” seems weird to me: who says they “approve of” another human being?
msgctxt "sn2.29:1.3"
msgid "“tuyhampi no, ānanda, sāriputto ruccatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Ānanda, do you like Sāriputta?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn2.29:2.1"
msgid "“Kassa hi nāma, bhante, abālassa aduṭṭhassa amūḷhassa avipallatthacittassa āyasmā sāriputto na rucceyya? "
msgstr "“Sir, who on earth would not like Venerable Sāriputta unless they’re a fool, a hater, delusional, or mentally deranged? "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.2"
msgid "Paṇḍito, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "Venerable Sāriputta is astute, "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.3"
msgid "Mahāpañño, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "he has great wisdom, "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.4"
msgid "Puthupañño, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "widespread wisdom, "

#. VAR: Hāsapañño → hāsupañño (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn2.29:2.5"
msgid "Hāsapañño, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "laughing wisdom, "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.6"
msgid "Javanapañño, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "swift wisdom, "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.7"
msgid "Tikkhapañño, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "sharp wisdom, "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.8"
msgid "Nibbedhikapañño, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "and penetrating wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.9"
msgid "Appiccho, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "He has few wishes, "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.10"
msgid "Santuṭṭho, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "he’s content, "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.11"
msgid "Pavivitto, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "secluded, "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.12"
msgid "Asaṃsaṭṭho, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "aloof, "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.13"
msgid "Āraddhavīriyo, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "and energetic. "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.14"
msgid "Vattā, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "He gives advice "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.15"
msgid "Vacanakkhamo, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "and accepts advice; "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.16"
msgid "Codako, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "he accuses "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.17"
msgid "Pāpagarahī, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "and criticizes wickedness. "

msgctxt "sn2.29:2.18"
msgid "Kassa hi nāma, bhante, abālassa aduṭṭhassa amūḷhassa avipallatthacittassa āyasmā sāriputto na rucceyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Who on earth would not like Venerable Sāriputta unless they’re a fool, a hater, delusional, or mentally deranged?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.64, pts2ed1.148, sc3
msgctxt "sn2.29:3.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, ānanda, evametaṃ, ānanda. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, Ānanda! That’s so true! "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.2"
msgid "Kassa hi nāma, ānanda, abālassa aduṭṭhassa amūḷhassa avipallatthacittassa sāriputto na rucceyya? "
msgstr "Who on earth would not like Venerable Sāriputta unless they’re a fool, a hater, delusional, or mentally deranged?” "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.3"
msgid "Paṇḍito, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr "And the Buddha repeated all of Ānanda’s terms of praise. "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.4"
msgid "Mahāpañño, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.5"
msgid "Puthupañño, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.6"
msgid "Hāsapañño, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.7"
msgid "Javanapañño, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.8"
msgid "Tikkhapañño, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.9"
msgid "Nibbedhikapañño, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.10"
msgid "Appiccho, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.11"
msgid "Santuṭṭho, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.12"
msgid "Pavivitto, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.13"
msgid "Asaṃsaṭṭho, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.14"
msgid "Āraddhavīriyo, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.15"
msgid "Vattā, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.16"
msgid "Vacanakkhamo, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.17"
msgid "Codako, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.18"
msgid "Pāpagarahī, ānanda, sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:3.19"
msgid "Kassa hi nāma, ānanda, abālassa aduṭṭhassa amūḷhassa avipallatthacittassa sāriputto na rucceyyā”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: susimo → susīmo (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn2.29:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho susimo devaputto āyasmato sāriputtassa vaṇṇe bhaññamāne mahatiyā devaputtaparisāya parivuto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho susimo devaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "While this praise of Sāriputta was being spoken, the god Susīma approached the Buddha, escorted by a large assembly of gods. He bowed, stood to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.149, sc5
msgctxt "sn2.29:5.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugata. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One! "

msgctxt "sn2.29:5.2"
msgid "Kassa hi nāma, bhante, abālassa aduṭṭhassa amūḷhassa avipallatthacittassa āyasmā sāriputto na rucceyya? "
msgstr "Who on earth would not like Venerable Sāriputta unless they’re a fool, a hater, delusional, or mentally deranged?” "

msgctxt "sn2.29:5.3"
msgid "Paṇḍito, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr "And he too repeated all the terms of praise of Sāriputta, adding, "

msgctxt "sn2.29:5.4"
msgid "Mahāpañño, bhante, puthupañño, bhante, hāsapañño, bhante, javanapañño, bhante, tikkhapañño, bhante, nibbedhikapañño, bhante, appiccho, bhante, santuṭṭho, bhante, pavivitto, bhante, asaṃsaṭṭho, bhante, āraddhavīriyo, bhante, vattā, bhante, vacanakkhamo, bhante, codako, bhante, pāpagarahī, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:5.5"
msgid "Kassa hi nāma, bhante, abālassa aduṭṭhassa amūḷhassa avipallatthacittassa āyasmā sāriputto na rucceyya? "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn2.29:6.1"
msgid "Ahampi hi, bhante, yaññadeva devaputtaparisaṃ upasaṅkamiṃ, etadeva bahulaṃ saddaṃ suṇāmi: "
msgstr "“For I too, sir, whenever I go to an assembly of gods, frequently hear the same terms of praise.” "

msgctxt "sn2.29:6.2"
msgid "‘paṇḍito āyasmā sāriputto; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:6.3"
msgid "mahāpañño āyasmā, puthupañño āyasmā, hāsapañño āyasmā, javanapañño āyasmā, tikkhapañño āyasmā, nibbedhikapañño āyasmā, appiccho āyasmā, santuṭṭho āyasmā, pavivitto āyasmā, asaṃsaṭṭho āyasmā, āraddhavīriyo āyasmā, vattā āyasmā, vacanakkhamo āyasmā, codako āyasmā, pāpagarahī āyasmā sāriputto’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn2.29:6.4"
msgid "Kassa hi nāma, bhante, abālassa aduṭṭhassa amūḷhassa avipallatthacittassa āyasmā sāriputto na rucceyyā”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn2.29:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho susimassa devaputtassa devaputtaparisā āyasmato sāriputtassa vaṇṇe bhaññamāne attamanā pamuditā pītisomanassajātā uccāvacā vaṇṇanibhā upadaṃseti. "
msgstr "While this praise of Sāriputta was being spoken, the gods of Susīma’s assembly—uplifted and overjoyed, full of rapture and happiness—generated a rainbow of bright colors. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.65, pts2ed1.150, sc8
msgctxt "sn2.29:8.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato paṇḍukambale nikkhitto bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca; "
msgstr "Suppose there was a beryl gem that was naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, well-worked. When placed on a cream rug it would shine and glow and radiate. "

msgctxt "sn2.29:8.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ susimassa devaputtassa devaputtaparisā āyasmato sāriputtassa vaṇṇe bhaññamāne attamanā pamuditā pītisomanassajātā uccāvacā vaṇṇanibhā upadaṃseti. "
msgstr "In the same way, the gods of Susīma’s assembly … generated a rainbow of bright colors. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn2.29:9.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma nikkhaṃ jambonadaṃ dakkhakammāraputtaukkāmukhasukusalasampahaṭṭhaṃ paṇḍukambale nikkhittaṃ bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca; "
msgstr "Suppose there was an ornament of rare gold, fashioned by an expert smith, well wrought in the forge. When placed on a cream rug it would shine and glow and radiate. "

msgctxt "sn2.29:9.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ susimassa devaputtassa devaputtaparisā āyasmato sāriputtassa vaṇṇe bhaññamāne attamanā pamuditā pītisomanassajātā uccāvacā vaṇṇanibhā upadaṃseti. "
msgstr "In the same way, the gods of Susīma’s assembly … generated a rainbow of bright colors. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn2.29:10.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma saradasamaye viddhe vigatavalāhake deve rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ osadhitārakā bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca; "
msgstr "Suppose that after the rainy season the sky was clear and cloudless. At the crack of dawn, the Morning Star shines and glows and radiates. "

msgctxt "sn2.29:10.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ susimassa devaputtassa devaputtaparisā āyasmato sāriputtassa vaṇṇe bhaññamāne attamanā pamuditā pītisomanassajātā uccāvacā vaṇṇanibhā upadaṃseti. "
msgstr "In the same way, the gods of Susīma’s assembly … generated a rainbow of bright colors. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.151, sc11
msgctxt "sn2.29:11.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma saradasamaye viddhe vigatavalāhake deve ādicco nabhaṃ abbhussakkamāno sabbaṃ ākāsagataṃ tamagataṃ abhivihacca bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca; "
msgstr "Suppose that after the rainy season the sky was clear and cloudless. As the sun rises, it would dispel all the darkness from the sky as it shines and glows and radiates. "

msgctxt "sn2.29:11.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ susimassa devaputtassa devaputtaparisā āyasmato sāriputtassa vaṇṇe bhaññamāne attamanā pamuditā pītisomanassajātā uccāvacā vaṇṇanibhā upadaṃseti. "
msgstr "In the same way, the gods of Susīma’s assembly … generated a rainbow of bright colors. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn2.29:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho susimo devaputto āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the god Susīma recited this verse about Venerable Sāriputta in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn2.29:13.1"
msgid "“Paṇḍitoti samaññāto, "
msgstr "“He’s considered to be an astute person, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.29:13.2"
msgid "sāriputto akodhano; "
msgstr "Sāriputta, free of anger. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.29:13.3"
msgid "Appiccho sorato danto, "
msgstr "Few in wishes, sweet, tamed, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.29:13.4"
msgid "satthuvaṇṇābhato isī”ti. "
msgstr "the hermit shines in the Teacher’s praise!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn2.29:14.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ ārabbha susimaṃ devaputtaṃ gāthāya paccabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha replied to Susīma with this verse about Venerable Sāriputta: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn2.29:15.1"
msgid "“Paṇḍitoti samaññāto, "
msgstr "“He’s considered to be an astute person, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.29:15.2"
msgid "sāriputto akodhano; "
msgstr "Sāriputta, free of anger. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.29:15.3"
msgid "Appiccho sorato danto, "
msgstr "Few in wishes, sweet, tamed; "

# NOTE: See BB for readings.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: kālaṃ kaṅkhati sudanto → kālaṃ kaṅkhati bhatako sudanto (si) | kālaṃ kaṅkhati bhāvito sudanto (s1-3, km) | kālaṃ kaṅkhati bhatiko sudanto (pts1) | kālaṃ kaṅkhati bhāvito (pts2)
msgctxt "sn2.29:15.4"
msgid "kālaṃ kaṅkhati sudanto”ti. "
msgstr "developed and well-tamed, he bides his time.”"

